Apparently, updateIssue will ignore any requests to set the status field of an issue - progressWorkflowAction should be used instead. Regardless of whether that's good or not, I've just blown 3 hours trying to work out why updateIssue was apparently not working; it wasn't until just now when I found CONF-6959 that I've fixed it.

The Javadocs for the RPC API need to be updated to include this info. They're pretty dire in general but this is *particularly* the kind of info that should be there. Just a note on updateIssue would do.

Also, less importantly, it would have been easier to catch this if the updateIssue call wasn't apparently succeeding. If updateIssue is called with a single RemoteField value of key 'status,' some kind of fault should be returned. (When 'status' is mixed in with other fields, it should possibly do it as well, but that might break code that is apparently 'working;' however, when status is the only field passed, the code must already be broken...)

