One of our typical usage scenarios is to run a a search either by using a saved filter or by clicking on a link with a underlying filter (project name, unresolved issues, ...) and afterwards limiting the search results even more by typing a few words from the description of the wanted issue. What I do now is editing the currently viewed query in the issue navigator, adding the filtering words (to the title and description textbox) and runing the query again.

I would like to save the editing of the current filter to limit its results with a fulltext string entry. Could the quick search work that way, that if a query has been run and the web GUI shows the results in the issue navigator, the quick search would work on the queried set of issues only, limiting the results yet more?

Clicking on the project name and using this "limiting quick search" could fix the issue JRA-15306 too.

